A popular television host, Funmi Iyanda will Anchor The Public Eye Season 2 packaged by Oya Media. The show will connects peoples with stories to share, experts and institutions to discuss contextual issues with the aim of seeking  innovative action. The official launch date for Public Eye Season 2 is June 23 on TVC.   Kumuyi’s forthrightness, integrity worthy of…     Fuel scarcity hits Lagos metropolis     PDP chieftain Okocha lauds Okowa’s VP candidacy   The Show, which is returning for its second season, has a rich array of topics and guests. The Show host, Funmi Iyanda and select guests with personal stories tackle perennial issues such as Corporal Punishment in Schools, Loan (app) sharks, insecurity, women inclusion, the japa trend, population explosion, renewable energy, Ibo apprenticeship system, rising food prices, Elections in Nigeria. The aim is a way forward. Public Eye season 2, powered by the MacArthur Foundation, will features guests from different parts of the country, government officials inclusive.